1 their official duties regularly places them in danger of death, serious physical
2 injury, and other reprisals from members of the public.
3 (b) Violence to and intimidation of such public servants and their families
4 is on the rise and public access to the personal information of these individuals
5 can be and has been used to facilitate violence and intimidation. The personal
6 information of these individuals is of negligible value to the public interest or
7 public discourse.
8 (c) Accordingly, the provisions of this act are both necessary and
9 appropriate to protect the privacy, safety, and security of public servants and to
10 prevent interference in the administration of justice and the operation of
11 government in the State of Vermont.
